<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="99" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1437,394,1033]" pageId="22" pageNumber="99">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,683,709]" pageId="22" pageNumber="99">Remarks:</emphasis>
A record from Chabahar Bay by 
<bibRefCitation author="Attaran-Fariman, G. &amp; Beygmoradi, A." box="[681,1120,683,710]" pageId="22" pageNumber="99" pagination="1254 - 1261" refId="ref13213" refString="Attaran-Fariman, G. &amp; Beygmoradi, A. (2016) Short communication: The first report of Amphipholis squamata (Delle Chiaje, 1829) (Echinodermata: Ophiuroidea) from Chabahar Bay - northern Oman Sea. Iranian Journal of Fisheries Sciences, 15, 1254 - 1261." type="journal article" year="2016">Attaran-Fariman &amp; Beygmoradi (2016)</bibRefCitation>
is an error and omitted here. Their images show an animal with narrow, sunken in radial shields (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ljungman" authorityYear="1866" box="[904,1046,719,745]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Amphiuridae" genus="Amphipholis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="22" pageNumber="99" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[904,1046,719,745]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="99">Amphipholis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has short, half-circle shaped ones), bell-shaped overlapping dorsal arm plates (separated in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="- Ljungman" authorityYear="1872" box="[770,910,755,781]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Amphiuridae" genus="Amphipholis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="22" pageNumber="99" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="squamata">
<emphasis box="[770,787,755,781]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="99">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[801,910,756,781]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="99">squamata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), small narrow tentacle scales (larger oval in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="- Ljungman" authorityYear="1872" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Amphiuridae" genus="Amphipholis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="22" pageNumber="99" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="squamata">
<emphasis box="[1412,1429,755,781]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="99">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[151,260,792,817]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="99">squamata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), widely separated infradental papillae (close together in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="- Ljungman" authorityYear="1872" box="[906,1046,791,817]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Amphiuridae" genus="Amphipholis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="22" pageNumber="99" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="squamata">
<emphasis box="[906,923,791,817]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="99">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[937,1046,792,817]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="99">squamata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and the distal oral papilla is only slightly widened, not as wide as in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="- Ljungman" authorityYear="1872" box="[552,693,827,853]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Amphiuridae" genus="Amphipholis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="22" pageNumber="99" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="squamata">
<emphasis box="[552,569,827,853]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="99">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[584,693,828,853]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="99">squamata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In addition, according to the scale bar on the images, the animal had a disc diameter of 
<quantity box="[405,472,863,889]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="22" pageNumber="99" unit="mm" value="8.0">8 mm</quantity>
, which is larger than 
<taxonomicName authorityName="- Ljungman" authorityYear="1872" box="[711,851,863,889]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Amphiuridae" genus="Amphipholis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="22" pageNumber="99" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="squamata">
<emphasis box="[711,728,863,889]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="99">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[742,851,864,889]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="99">squamata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(maximum 
<quantity box="[988,1057,862,889]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="22" pageNumber="99" unit="mm" value="5.0">5 mm</quantity>
), and they reported the arms to be 
<quantity box="[151,207,899,925]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="22" pageNumber="99" unit="cm" value="6.0">6 cm</quantity>
long, whereas 
<taxonomicName authorityName="- Ljungman" authorityYear="1872" box="[380,521,899,925]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Amphiuridae" genus="Amphipholis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="22" pageNumber="99" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="squamata">
<emphasis box="[380,397,899,925]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="99">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[412,521,900,925]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="99">squamata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has about 
<quantity box="[644,700,899,925]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="22" pageNumber="99" unit="cm" value="2.0">2 cm</quantity>
long arms. The characters fit with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Verrill" authorityYear="1899" box="[1097,1220,899,925]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Amphiuridae" genus="Amphiodia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="22" pageNumber="99" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1097,1220,899,925]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="99">Amphiodia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the images do not show the necessary details for species identification. Consequently, the material found by the present study is the first record of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="- Ljungman" authorityYear="1872" box="[350,489,971,997]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Amphiuridae" genus="Amphipholis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="22" pageNumber="99" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="squamata">
<emphasis box="[350,367,971,997]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="99">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[380,489,972,997]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="99">squamata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Gulf of 
<collectingCountry box="[683,755,971,997]" name="Oman" pageId="22" pageNumber="99">Oman</collectingCountry>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="- Ljungman" authorityYear="1872" box="[764,1021,971,997]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Amphiuridae" genus="Amphipholis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="22" pageNumber="99" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="squamata">
<emphasis box="[764,1021,971,997]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="99">Amphipholis squamata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a circumtropical distribution, but it is most likely a species complex (
<bibRefCitation author="Sponer, R. &amp; Roy, M. S." box="[550,781,1007,1033]" pageId="22" pageNumber="99" pagination="1954 - 1967" refId="ref18427" refString="Sponer, R. &amp; Roy, M. S. (2002) Phylogeographic analysis of the brooding brittle star Amphipholis squamata (Echinodermata) along the coast of New Zealand reveals high cryptic variation and cryptic dispersal potential. Evolution, 56, 1954 - 1967." type="journal article" year="2002">Sponer &amp; Roy 2002</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Boissin, E. &amp; Egea, E. &amp; Feral, J. P. &amp; Chenuil, A." box="[791,1006,1006,1033]" pageId="22" pageNumber="99" pagination="165 - 177" refId="ref13565" refString="Boissin, E., Egea, E., Feral, J. P. &amp; Chenuil, A. (2015) Contrasting population genetic structures in Amphipholis squamata, a complex of brooding, self-reproducing sister species sharing life history traits. Marine Ecology Progress Series, 539, 165 - 177. https: // doi. org / 10.3354 / meps 11480" type="journal article" year="2015">
Boissin 
<emphasis box="[882,939,1007,1033]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="99">et al.</emphasis>
2015
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
